      • dataSourceReader

        public ObjectDataSourceBuilder dataSourceReader(DataSourceReader reader)
        Specify the DataSourceReader that contains the inputStream for this ObjectDataSource. Typically, this DataSourceReader is created using a RestRequestBuilder.
        Parameters:
        reader - the DataSourceReader containing the input for this ObjectDataSource
        Returns:
        the current ObjectDataSourceBuilder

      • resultList

        public ObjectDataSourceBuilder resultList(javafx.collections.ObservableList<T> list)
        The resulting entities for the ObjectDataSource created by this builder will be added by the supplied ObservableList. If this method is not called, the ObjectDataSource will create an own, empty ObservableList instance.
        This method is particularly useful in case the entities obtained via this ObjectDataSource need to be merged with existing entities.
        Parameters:
        list - the ObservableList that will be populated with the obtained elements. This list is not cleared, hence all existing elements in the list will be kept.
        Returns:
        the current ObjectDataSourceBuilder

      • resultObject

        public ObjectDataSourceBuilder resultObject(javafx.beans.property.ObjectProperty<T> target)
        In case the result of the data-retrieval is a single Object, an ObjectProperty should be passed here. Once the data is retrieved, this ObjectProperty will contain the data
        Parameters:
        target - the ObjectProperty that will contain the retrieved data
        Returns:

      • columns

        public ObjectDataSourceBuilder columns(String... columns)
        Specify which columns should be taken into account when creating a TableView based on the items in this ObjectDataSource.
        Valid column names are JavaBean properties (e.g. if the class specified via the itemClass method contains a method setFoo, "foo" is a valid column name.
        Parameters:
        columns - A list of String instances, defining the column names.
        Returns:
